page.title: 19WILD FLOWERS ON OTMOOR
page.content: We visited an area between a track (Roman road) and a drainage dyke. JUNE 10th. Bush Vetch, Forget-me-not, Creeping Buttercup, Hedge Parsley, Cut-leaved Cranesbill, Herb Robert, Horehound, Horse Radish, Meadowsweet, Meadow Vetchling, Shepherd's Purse, Ragged Robin, Red Clover, Sowthistle, Smooth Tare, Lesser Yellow Trefoil, White Dead Nettle. JULY 15th. Bird's Foot Trefoil,Bramble, Bittersweet, Corn Chamomile, Creeping Cinquefoil, Forget-me-not, Cut Leaved Cranesbill, Dandelion, Dog Rose, Great Plantain, Goosegrass, Great Willowherb Long Headed Poppy, Hedge Parsley, Hedge Bindweed, Hogweed, Hedge Woundwort, Horse Radish, Red Clover, Meadowsweet, Meadow Vetchling, Silverweed, Perforated St.John's Wort, Tufted Vetch, White Dead Nettle, Shepherd's Purse, Thistle.
